    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA109-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai āṟṟāḷāya talaimakaḷatu (ET: talaiviyatu) nilai kaṇṭa (ET: kaṇṭu varuntiya) tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu (ET: coṟṟatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to [her] confidante who saw state of HER who unable to bear it in the time of separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA109">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            oṉṟutu meṉṟa toṉṟupaṭu naṭpiṟ</l>
<l>            kātala rakaṉṟeṉak kalaṅkip pētuṟ</l>
<l>            ṟaṉṉa tōvin naṉṉuta ṉilaiyeṉa</l>
<l>            viṉava lāṉāp puṉaiyiḻai kēḷiṉi</l>
<l>            yuraikka lākā vevva mimmeṉa </l>
<l>            viraikkum vāṭai yiruḷkūr poḻutiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟoḷiyuṭait toḻuviṟ ṟuṇita laṟṟat</l>
<l>            tuccik kaṭṭiya kūḻai yāvi</l>
<l>            ṉilaiyeṉa voruvē ṉāki</l>
<l>            yulamarak kaḻiyumip pakaṉmaṭi poḻutē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>[O you of] adorning jewels who do not stop asking:</l>
<l rend="indent2">"being confused [and] agitated because [your] lover departed,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in intimacy bound of old that said “we will be one”,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[is] thus the state of this good forehead?",</l>
<l rend="indent4">listen now,</l>
<l>– the drooping time of this midday passes by perturbingly,</l>
<l rend="indent">since I own that the state</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the small(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kūḻai</term>: what does this attribute refer to in connection with a cow? That she is small of growth? That she is mal-nourished?</note> cow tied by the head(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ucci</term>, usually "summit", is here explained by T.V.G. to mean something like "rafter". Why, however, not take it as the summit of the cow, that is, its head?</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">[is] one that destroys resolution(?), in a manger full of mire,</l>
<l>at a time abounding in darkness [and] north wind that cries out</l>
<l rend="indent3">'im', with trouble that is not told.</l>
        </lg>
